<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Object Oriented Programming | Smart Academy</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.4/css/all.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/oop.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/navbar.css">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/Photos/smart_academy-updated.png">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <img class="logo-img" src="/Photos/smart_academy-updated.png" alt="Smart Academy Logo" onclick="window.location.href='/home'"> 
    <h2>Object Oriented Programming</h2>
  </header>

  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/home">Home</a>
      <a href="/courses">Courses</a>
      <a href="/aboutUs">About Us</a>
      <a href="/contactUs">Contact</a>
      <%- include('partials/cart') %>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-auth">
      <% if (user) { %>
        <% if (user.isAdmin) { %>
          <a href="admin/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary me-2">Dashboard</a>
        <% } %>
        <button id="logoutBtn">Logout</button>
      <% } else { %>
        <a href="/signlog" class="auth-btn">Sign Up</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div id="cartModal" class="modal">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <span class="close">&times;</span>
      <h2 class="modalTitle">Shopping Cart</h2>
      <div id="cartItems"></div>
      <div class="cart-total">
        <strong>Total: </strong>
        <span id="cartTotal">$0</span>
      </div>
      <button id="checkoutBtn" class="checkout-btn">
        Proceed to Checkout
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="course-banner">
    <img src="/Photos/1677400884011.jfif" alt="Object Oriented Programming Course" class="course-image">
    <div class="banner-overlay">
      <h1>Full OOP Course for Beginners</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- âœ… Embedded YouTube Video Section -->
  <section class="course-video">
    <h2 style="text-align:center; margin: 30px 0;">Course Introduction Video</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center;">
      <iframe width="860" height="480"
        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SiBw7os-_zI"
        title="OOP Full Course"
        frameborder="0"
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen>
      </iframe>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="course-content">
    <section class="overview">
      <h2>Course Overview</h2>
      <p>Master Object-Oriented Programming principles and concepts with our comprehensive course.</p>
      <div class="course-meta">
        <span class="rating">
          <i class="fas fa-star"></i> 4.5
          <small>(2,234 ratings)</small>
        </span>
        <span class="students">
          <i class="fas fa-users"></i> 53,280 students
        </span>
        <span class="instructor">
          <i class="fas fa-chalkboard-teacher"></i> Eng. Robert Lafore
        </span>
        <span class="language">
          <i class="fas fa-globe"></i> English, Arabic
        </span>
        <span class="last-updated">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Last updated 22/3/2025
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="course-actions">
        <button class="add-to-cart" data-course="oop" data-price="599">
          <i class="fas fa-cart-plus"></i>
          Add to Cart - $599
        </button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="what-you-learn">
      <h2>What You'll Learn</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Core principles of OOP: encapsulation, inheritance, abstraction, and polymorphism</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Design and structure programs using classes and objects</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Real-world OOP applications and implementations</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Constructors, access modifiers, and method overloading</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Debug and test OOP-based applications</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> OOP in Java, Python, and C++</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Model complex systems using object-oriented design</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Interfaces and abstract classes</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="course-includes">
      <h2>This Course Includes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-video"></i> 20 basic lectures</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-tasks"></i> 11 assignments per lecture</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-redo"></i> Recap videos</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Quizzes after each lecture</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-certificate"></i> Certificate of completion</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-infinity"></i> Full lifetime access</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="learning-outcomes">
      <h2>By The End Of This Course You Will Be Able To</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Master the basics of Object-Oriented Programming</li>
        <li>Handle problems using inheritance and polymorphism</li>
        <li>Design and implement complex object-oriented systems</li>
        <li>Write clean, maintainable, and reusable code</li>
        <li>Apply OOP principles in real-world projects</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
  </div>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>

  <script src="/js/oop.js"></script>
  <script src="/js/logOut.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
